6.title: Industry Links
6.text:
Canadian crude is an attractive alternative to imported oil

Canada has the third-largest oil reserves in the world, but we import large volumes of oil from foreign sources into Eastern Canada, including Quebec, every day.

www.capp.ca

Nova Scotia should revisit fracking ban

The Nova Scotia government’s decision to effectively ban the use of hydraulic fracturing is unnecessary and will preclude Nova Scotians from benefitting from the responsible development of their onshore natural gas resource.

www.capp.ca

Grande Prairie: Resourceful and growing

Q: How would you describe the economic health of Grande Prairie? A: Very active and robust — almost explosive. There’s so much opportunity...

www.financialpost.com

Fort St. John’s vibrancy and growth is fuelled by the natural gas industry

For Fort St. John, the energy capital of B.C., the boom times began in the 1950s with the discovery of petroleum.

www.financialpost.com

Fracopedia

A resource created and designed to answer your questions about hydraulic fracturing in Canada.

www.oilandgasinfo.ca

Presented by:

7.title: Water Use
7.text:
Environmental Priority Area: Water

Water is a high-value commodity and COSIA is looking for innovative and sustainable solutions to reduce water use and increase water recycling rates.

www.cosia.ca

COSIA's Water Performance Goal

Canada's Oil Sands Innovation Alliance members with in situ operations will strive to reduce fresh water use intensity by 50 per cent by 2022.

www.cosia.ca

Waste water from Alberta’s oil sands being reused

Saltworks Technologies show us how the Saltmaker takes in low-grade heat energy and high-saline wastewater and produces distilled water.

www.youtube.com

Regulating and Monitoring: Water

Learn about the regulations and monitoring oil sands producers must adhere to as a part of the oil sands development process.

www.oilsandstoday.ca

Topics of Interest: Water Use

As the oil sands industry grows, so does the demand on Canadian water resources.

www.oilsandstoday.ca

Presented by:
